## UI Design Principles

### 1. Beautiful and Vibrant UI
- Use vibrant colors from the design system
- Create engaging, modern interfaces
- Follow mobile-first design principles
- Ensure excellent user experience

### 2. Consistency
- Use the same spacing, colors, and typography throughout the app
- Follow established patterns from existing components
- Maintain visual hierarchy

### 3. Responsive Design
- Use SafeAreaView for proper spacing

## Style File Structure

### Styling Constants (`constants/styling/`)
- `colors.ts` - Color definitions and utilities
- `spacings.ts` - Margin and padding utilities
- `fonts.ts` - Typography utilities

### Component Styles (`components/*/styles.ts`)
```typescript
import { StyleSheet } from 'react-native';
import { AppColors } from '@/constants/styling/colors';
import { Spacings } from '@/constants/styling/spacings';
import { FontSizes } from '@/constants/styling/fonts';

export const styles = StyleSheet.create({
  container: {
    backgroundColor: AppColors.WHITE,
    padding: Spacings.STANDART,
    borderRadius: 8,
  },
  title: {
    fontSize: FontSizes.LARGE,
    color: AppColors.PRIMARY,
    fontWeight: 'bold',
  },
});
```

## Examples

### Good Styling Pattern
```typescript
import { AppColors, Spacings } from '@/constants/styling';

const MyComponent = () => {
  return (
    <View style={[styles.container]}>
      <Text style={styles.title}>Title</Text>
    </View>
  );
};

const styles = StyleSheet.create({
  container: {
    padding: Spacings.SMALL,
  },
  title: {
    fontSize: FontSizes.MEDIUM,
    color: AppColors.PRIMARY,
  },
});
```

### Anti-Patterns to Avoid

❌ **Don't hardcode colors, use AppColors**
❌ **Don't hardcode spacing, use Spacings**
❌ **Don't hardcode font sizes, use FontSizes**
❌ **Don't duplicate style definitions across components**
